15/11/2009
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor announced on Friday (November 13th) that she is appointing Djuro Popijac as economy minister. Popijac, president of the Croatian Employers' Association, replaces Damir Polancec, who resigned at the end of October as a result of a corporate scandal in food company Podravka. Kosor announced two cabinet changes also driven by his resignation. Health Minister Darko Milinovic and Finance Minister Ivan Suker will become deputy prime ministers, while retaining their portfolios. (HRT, Poslovni, Dnevnik, Javno - 13/11/09)
